From: GoByte Core Developers <dev@gobyte.network>
Subject: [PATCH] qt 5.9.6 win32: guard tagTOUCHINPUT typedef against mingw-w64 11.x

mingw-w64 >= 11.0 declares tagTOUCHINPUT / TOUCHINPUT / PTOUCHINPUT
unconditionally in winuser.h when _WIN32_WINNT >= 0x0601.  Qt 5.9.6's
qwindowsmousehandler.cpp re-declares the same struct unconditionally as
a compatibility shim for older SDK headers that lacked it.  On Ubuntu
24.04 the newer mingw-w64 headers expose the conflict as a hard
multiple-definition error:

  qwindowsmousehandler.cpp:65:16: error: redefinition of 'struct tagTOUCHINPUT'
  qwindowsmousehandler.cpp:76:3:  error: conflicting declaration 'typedef int TOUCHINPUT'

WM_TOUCH (0x0240) is defined in every winuser.h version that provides
the full touch-input API surface (TOUCHINPUT, TOUCHEVENTF_*, etc.).
Guard the compatibility block on !defined(WM_TOUCH) so the shim is
emitted only for SDK headers that need it.

Observed: Ubuntu 24.04 / mingw-w64 11.0 / x86_64-w64-mingw32
          (GitHub Actions ubuntu-latest, 2026-Q1)
---
 qtbase/src/plugins/platforms/windows/qwindowsmousehandler.cpp | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

--- a/qtbase/src/plugins/platforms/windows/qwindowsmousehandler.cpp
+++ b/qtbase/src/plugins/platforms/windows/qwindowsmousehandler.cpp
@@ -64,0 +65 @@
+#ifndef WM_TOUCH
@@ -76,0 +78 @@
+#endif /* WM_TOUCH */
